SIMPLE: twittering
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Twittering
<hw>Twit"ter*ing</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of one
who, or that which, twitters.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A slight nervous excitement or agitation, such as is
caused by desire, expectation, or suspense.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A widow, who had a <qex>twittering</qex> towards a second husband,
took a gossiping companion to manage the job.</q>
<rj><qau>L'Estrange.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Twittingly</ent>⟦br⟧
